[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    266[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    267[0m:[38;5;10m[49m Two options.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    268[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    269[0m:[38;5;10m[49m Option A (lower-touch, matches the recipe's "one item per turn" framing): expand the protocol's question-flow at design time so each screener item is its own entry. For PHQ-2:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    270[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    271[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ```python
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    272[0m:[38;5;10m[49m {"id": "phq2_q1", "category": "screener",
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    273[0m:[38;5;10m[49m  "screener_id": "PHQ-2", "item_id": "phq2_q1"},
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    274[0m:[38;5;10m[49m {"id": "phq2_q2", "category": "screener",
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    275[0m:[38;5;10m[49m  "screener_id": "PHQ-2", "item_id": "phq2_q2"},
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    276[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ```
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    277[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    278[0m:[38;5;10m[49m After all items for a screener are captured, an additional state-machine action computes the score and appends a `screener_record` to the session. This is cleaner architecturally because the state machine remains "one question per turn" and the screener registry can declare its items independently.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    279[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    280[0m:[38;5;10m[49m Option B (higher-touch, but matches the recipe's "screener as a single tool that administers a bundle" framing): treat the screener entry as a sub-flow that the orchestration loop runs as a nested state. The state machine, when it encounters a screener entry, transitions to a `screener_admin` substate that walks the items one per turn before resuming the parent flow. `_compute_screener_score` is called at substate-exit time and the result is appended to `session.screener_records`.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    281[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    282[0m:[38;5;10m[49m Either fix produces the expected demo output. After the fix, hand-tracing the headline scenario:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    283[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    284[0m:[38;5;10m[49m - The PHQ-2 questions are administered one at a time across two turns.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    285[0m:[38;5;10m[49m - Both response values are captured as `screener_item_response` findings.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    286[0m:[38;5;10m[49m - `_compute_screener_score("PHQ-2", [{response_value: 0}, {response_value: 0}])` returns `{score: 0, band: "negative"}`.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    287[0m:[38;5;10m[49m - A `screener_record` is appended to `session.screener_records`.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    288[0m:[38;5;10m[49m - The packet's `screeners` field has the PHQ-2 record. The closing summary's "PHQ-2 score: 0 (negative)" line appears.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    289[0m:[38;5;10m[49m - The audit record's `screener_records_summary` matches the recipe's sample.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    290[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    291[0m:[38;5;10m[49m The screener-library entry for PHQ-9 has a similar latent issue: it lists only item 9 (the crisis-sensitive one) and not items 1-8. The demo never administers PHQ-9 (the protocol does not include it), so this does not surface, but a future protocol that includes PHQ-9 would have the same single-item pickup problem unless one of the two fix options above is in place. Worth noting in the same fix pass.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    292[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    293[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ---
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    294[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    295[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ### E3. Branch questions are appended to the END of the question flow, after `closing_confirmation`, rather than inserted at the right protocol position; the demo's chest-symptoms branch asks `hpi_severity` and `hpi_alleviating_factors` AFTER the bot has already wrapped up the conversation with the closing question
