[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    356[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    357[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **How to fix:**
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    358[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    359[0m:[38;5;10m[49m Two options.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    360[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    361[0m:[38;5;10m[49m Option A (matches the recipe's "interleave branch into the HPI section" framing): the protocol's branch definitions declare an `insert_after` field (or an `insert_before` field) referencing a base-flow question id. `_question_flow_state_machine` builds `full_flow` by inserting each triggered branch's questions at the declared position rather than appending them. For example:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    362[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    363[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ```python
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    364[0m:[38;5;10m[49m "branches": {
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    365[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     "chest_symptoms": {
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    366[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         "trigger_keywords":
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    367[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             ["chest", "tightness", "pressure"],
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    368[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         "insert_after": "hpi_associated",
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    369[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         "additional_questions": [
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    370[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             {"id": "hpi_severity", "category": "hpi",
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    371[0m:[38;5;10m[49m              "dimension": "severity"},
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    372[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             {"id": "hpi_alleviating_factors",
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    373[0m:[38;5;10m[49m              "category": "hpi",
