[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    544[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    545[0m:[38;5;10m[49m The "summarizes what has been captured" implies the bot knows where the patient left off. With the stale position, the resumed bot asks the just-answered question rather than the next one, which contradicts "graceful."
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    546[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    547[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **How to fix:**
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    548[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    549[0m:[38;5;10m[49m Reorder: update `protocol_position` (and `in_flight_question`) on the session row BEFORE persisting partial state. The simplest reordering:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    550[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    551[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ```python
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    552[0m:[38;5;10m[49m # Step 3B: ask the state machine for the next question.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    553[0m:[38;5;10m[49m next_step = _question_flow_state_machine(session=session)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    554[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    555[0m:[38;5;10m[49m if next_step.get("action") == "complete":
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    556[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     return _assemble_and_deliver_packet(...)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    557[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    558[0m:[38;5;10m[49m next_question = next_step["question"]
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    559[0m:[38;5;10m[49m _update_session_field(
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    560[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     session_id, "in_flight_question", next_question)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    561[0m:[38;5;10m[49m _update_session_field(
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    562[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     session_id, "protocol_position",
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    563[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     next_step["protocol_position"])
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    564[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    565[0m:[38;5;10m[49m # Persist partial state for resume AFTER advancing.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    566[0m:[38;5;10m[49m _persist_partial_state(_session_state(session_id))
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    567[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ```
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    568[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    569[0m:[38;5;10m[49m Also persist `in_flight_question` in the partial-state record so the resume path can short-circuit on the next message (the resumed bot can either re-ask the in-flight question conversationally or simply trust that the state machine will return it again at the same position). Currently `_persist_partial_state` does not include `in_flight_question` at all:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    570[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    571[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ```python
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    572[0m:[38;5;10m[49m def _persist_partial_state(session):
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    573[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     ...
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    574[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     table.put_item(Item=_to_decimal({
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    575[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         "encounter_id":      encounter_id,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    576[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         "patient_id":        patient_id,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    577[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         "session_id":        session["session_id"],
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    578[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         "protocol_position": session.get(
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    579[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             "protocol_position", 0),
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    580[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         "captured_findings": session.get(
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    581[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             "captured_findings", {}),
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    582[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         "screener_records":  session.get(
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    583[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             "screener_records", []),
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    584[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         "active_protocol":   session.get("active_protocol"),
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    585[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         "encounter_context": session.get(
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    586[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             "encounter_context"),
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    587[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         "chart_context":     session.get("chart_context"),
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    588[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         "context_loaded":    session.get(
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    589[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             "context_loaded", False),
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    590[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         ...
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    591[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     }))
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    592[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ```
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    593[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    594[0m:[38;5;10m[49m Add `"in_flight_question": session.get("in_flight_question")` so resume can pick up exactly where the patient left off.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    595[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    596[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ---
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    597[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    598[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ### W3. Several assistant-turn paths bypass `_screen_output` entirely; the conversation log captures the unscreened text and the audit pipeline never sees that the static template was the actual delivered text vs an LLM-replaced one
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    599[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    600[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **File / section:** `chapter11.04-python-example.md`, multiple call sites:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    601[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    602[0m:[38;5;10m[49m - `_handle_unauthenticated` — `_append_turn(speaker="assistant", text=PORTAL_LOGIN_REQUIRED_TEMPLATE, ...)` then `_build_chat_reply`. No screen.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    603[0m:[38;5;10m[49m - `_handle_screening_action` for `injection_refusal` and `phi_redirect` — `_append_turn(...)` with the template. No screen.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    604[0m:[38;5;10m[49m - `_route_crisis` — `_append_turn(..., text=template, ...)`. No screen.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    605[0m:[38;5;10m[49m - `_handle_intake_message` for the `intake_paused` branch — `_build_chat_reply(response_text=...)` with no `_append_turn` AND no screen.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    606[0m:[38;5;10m[49m - `_conduct_intake_turn` for the `ask_clarifying` branch — `_build_chat_reply(response_text=CLARIFY_EXTRACTION_TEMPLATE, ...)` with no `_append_turn` and no screen.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    607[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    608[0m:[38;5;10m[49m The screened paths are only:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    609[0m:[38;5;10m[49m - `_conduct_intake_turn` for the `asked_next_question` branch — `response_text = _phrase_question_conversationally(...)`, then `_screen_output`, then `_append_turn`. Correctly screened.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    610[0m:[38;5;10m[49m - `_assemble_and_deliver_packet` — closing summary built via `_build_closing_summary`, then `_screen_output`, then `_append_turn`. Correctly screened.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    611[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    612[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **What's wrong:**
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    613[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    614[0m:[38;5;10m[49m Same shape as 11.02 W4 / 11.03 W3, but with a different concrete impact. The static-template paths in 11.04 are clinical-leadership-reviewed templates (per the recipe's prose), so they do not need to be screened for clinical-advice or chart-fact violations. That part is fine.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    615[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    616[0m:[38;5;10m[49m The bug that does manifest is the audit gap on the `ask_clarifying` and `intake_paused` branches: those paths return `_build_chat_reply` without ever calling `_append_turn`, so the assistant's clarification/paused-acknowledgment message is never persisted to `conversation_metadata`. The conversation log becomes asymmetric — user messages are appended but the bot's responses to them are not. The audit record's `turn_count` undercounts the bot's actual messages, the cohort-stratified metrics are computed against an incomplete log, and a reviewer pulling up the conversation in the QA queue sees the user asking something with no response shown, even though one was delivered.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    617[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    618[0m:[38;5;10m[49m I traced this against an extension of the demo's headline scenario where the patient gives an unparseable HPI answer (e.g., "uhh"). `hpi_extraction_tool` returns `{"action": "ask_clarification", ...}` (it actually doesn't currently — see N1 below — but if it did): `_conduct_intake_turn` returns:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    619[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    620[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ```python
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    621[0m:[38;5;10m[49m return _build_chat_reply(
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    622[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     session_id=session_id,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    623[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     response_text=CLARIFY_EXTRACTION_TEMPLATE,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    624[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     attach_greeting=attach_initial_greeting,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    625[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     attach_resume=attach_resume_greeting,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    626[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     disposition="clarification_requested")
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    627[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ```
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    628[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    629[0m:[38;5;10m[49m No `_append_turn(speaker="assistant", text=CLARIFY_EXTRACTION_TEMPLATE, ...)`. The user's "uhh" is logged. The bot's "I want to make sure I have that right..." is not. On the next turn, the user's reply is logged. The audit reads as if the bot vanished for one turn.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    630[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    631[0m:[38;5;10m[49m The recipe's audit-pipeline narrative explicitly says:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    632[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    633[0m:[38;5;10m[49m > User utterances ... Generated bot responses
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    634[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    635[0m:[38;5;10m[49m The narrative implies symmetric logging. The current implementation breaks symmetry on at least two paths.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    636[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    637[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **How to fix:**
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    638[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    639[0m:[38;5;10m[49m Two structural fixes:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    640[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    641[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 1. Centralize assistant-turn writes through a single helper that handles append + screen + reply, similar to 11.02/11.03's recommended pattern but adapted to 11.04's mix of static-template and LLM-generated paths:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    642[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    643[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ```python
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    644[0m:[38;5;10m[49m def _append_assistant_turn_and_reply(
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    645[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         session_id, channel, response_text,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    646[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         attach_greeting, attach_resume, disposition,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    647[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         language, screen=True, **turn_extras):
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    648[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     final_text = response_text
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    649[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     if screen:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    650[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         screened = _screen_output(
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    651[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             session_id=session_id,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    652[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             response_text=response_text)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    653[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         if screened["action"] == "replace_with_safe_response":
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    654[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             final_text = screened["response_text"]
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    655[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             disposition = "output_replaced"
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    656[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     _append_turn(session_id, {
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    657[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         "speaker":   "assistant",
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    658[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         "text":      final_text,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    659[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         "timestamp": _now_iso(),
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    660[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         "language":  language,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    661[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         **turn_extras,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    662[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     })
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    663[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     return _build_chat_reply(
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    664[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         session_id=session_id,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    665[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         response_text=final_text,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    666[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         attach_greeting=attach_greeting,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    667[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         attach_resume=attach_resume,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    668[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         disposition=disposition)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    669[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ```
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    670[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    671[0m:[38;5;10m[49m Static-template paths set `screen=False`. LLM-generated paths set `screen=True`. Every assistant turn lands in the audit log either way.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    672[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    673[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 2. Replace the `ask_clarifying`, `intake_paused`, and similar early-return `_build_chat_reply` calls with the new helper.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    674[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    675[0m:[38;5;10m[49m The `_handle_unauthenticated`, `_handle_screening_action` injection/phi paths, and `_route_crisis` already call `_append_turn` correctly, so they only need a minor refactor to use the helper for consistency.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    676[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    677[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ---
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    678[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    679[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ## NOTE Findings
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    680[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    681[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ### N1. The per-category extraction tools never return `ask_clarification` for ambiguous answers; the only branch that triggers clarification is "empty answer text"
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    682[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    683[0m:[38;5;10m[49m `hpi_extraction_tool`, `ros_extraction_tool`, `medication_reconciliation_capture_tool`, `allergy_reconciliation_capture_tool`, `history_extraction_tool` all share the same shape:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    684[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    685[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ```python
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    686[0m:[38;5;10m[49m text = (answer_text or "").strip()
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    687[0m:[38;5;10m[49m if not text:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    688[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     return {"action": "ask_clarification", "finding": None}
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    689[0m:[38;5;10m[49m finding = {...}
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    690[0m:[38;5;10m[49m return {"action": "captured", "finding": finding}
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    691[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ```
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    692[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    693[0m:[38;5;10m[49m The only condition that returns clarification is an empty string. Every non-empty answer is captured, regardless of how nonsensical or incomplete. A patient who types "uhh" or "I don't know" or "what?" gets captured as a valid HPI/history/medication finding. The downstream packet has the noise as a structured finding.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    694[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    695[0m:[38;5;10m[49m The recipe's main-text emphasizes that the extraction tool "validates against the schema. If the answer is unparseable, the tool returns 'ask_clarification' and the conversation loop asks a follow-up." The demo's tools never do this. The `EXTRACTION_CONFIDENCE_THRESHOLD = Decimal("0.70")` constant in the configuration is never compared against any confidence score because no extraction tool produces one.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    696[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    697[0m:[38;5;10m[49m Fix: each extraction tool should produce a confidence score (production via the LLM; demo via simple heuristics) and return `ask_clarification` when the score is below `EXTRACTION_CONFIDENCE_THRESHOLD`. Even a few simple heuristics would make the demo more honest:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    698[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    699[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ```python
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    700[0m:[38;5;10m[49m # HPI: too short to be informative
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    701[0m:[38;5;10m[49m if len(text.split()) < 3:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    702[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     return {"action": "ask_clarification", "finding": None}
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    703[0m:[38;5;10m[49m # History family-cardiac: doesn't mention any relevant terms
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    704[0m:[38;5;10m[49m if history_dimension == "family_cardiac" and \
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    705[0m:[38;5;10m[49m    not any(t in lowered for t in
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    706[0m:[38;5;10m[49m        ["heart", "cardiac", "stroke", "blood pressure",
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    707[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         "diabetes", "no", "none", "don't know"]):
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    708[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     return {"action": "ask_clarification", "finding": None}
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    709[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ```
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    710[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    711[0m:[38;5;10m[49m The current behavior teaches a misleading pattern. A learner reading the code might assume "captured" means "high-confidence" and propagate that assumption.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    712[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    713[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ### N2. `screener_administer_tool_capture_item` defaults to `items[0]` when `item_id` is None, but the function does not warn or log; the silent default is the mechanism behind E2
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    714[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    715[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ```python
